icipation by academic staff members in external activities that enhance their professional skills or constitute public service can be beneficial to the university as well as to the individual. Because external activities can lead to conflicts of commitment or interest with regard to one’s university responsibilities, the non-university activities must be measured and monitored.         coi           START myDisclosures             myFCOI Checklist             Policy Overview           Announcement and Deadlines       Information for Campus Research Restart    Posted on April 28, 2020        CCTS Pilot Funding for COVID-19    Posted on April 14, 2020        Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research UPDATE – Friday, March 20, 2020 - 5:25pm    Posted on March 20, 2020        Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research UPDATE – March 19, 2020, 4:25pm    Posted on March 19, 2020        COVID-19 Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research Update - March 17, 2020    Posted on March 17, 2020         More Events and Deadlines             Conflict of Commitment & Interest (COI)    Back to main content           START myDisclosures    myFCOI Checklist    Report of Non-University Activities (RNUA)     RNUA Administrators Resources    RNUA Training Sessions      Sponsor Specific Disclosure    Managing Conflicts     How Can Conflicts of Interest Be Managed?    What is the Process in Creating a Management Plan?    Guidelines to Develop SFI-DMP    FAQs: SFI-DMP    FAQs: COI Related to SBIR and STTR Programs    FAQs: Physician Payments Sunshine Act    Guidance for Disclosing Foreign Interests      Conflict Review Committee     CRC Meeting Dates & Deadlines      Policies & Regulations    Resources for Business Managers     Business Manager log-in      Contact Us                   UIC Logo         Office Of  The Vice  Chancellor  For  Research                   Contact   Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research  1737 West Polk Street, Suite 310, MC 672, Chicago, IL 60612  Phone: (312